message:
fix(degradation): prevent callback reentrancy deadlock in policy notification

Release the policies lock before calling policy.apply() to prevent
self-deadlock if any DegradationPolicy implementation calls back into
DegradationFsm::tick(), add_policy(), or transition_count().

Pattern: clone Arc pointers, drop lock, then iterate.

Before (latent deadlock):
  let policies = self.policies.lock();
  for policy in policies.iter() {
      policy.apply(headroom);  // lock still held
  }

After (safe):
  let policies: Vec<_> = self.policies.lock().iter().cloned().collect();
  for policy in policies {
      policy.apply(headroom);  // lock released
  }

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>

